# NO BYTE-IDENTITY SEAL AT THE B5 SUB-RUNG — BY DESIGN.
#
# gmp-glibc is built by R12 (stage0-gcc-15.2.0, a DIFFERENT — musl-linked — compiler) than the
# debian-prebuilt-gcc-built production gmp, so byte-identity to production's artifact is EXPLICITLY
# not expected (b4-b7-readiness risk #3).  No `sha256sum -c` gate at the tail of build.sh.
#
# Invariants this rung DOES enforce (fail-shut, in build.sh):
#   * upstream `make check` (production parity) — the full GMP testsuite against the fresh lib;
#   * B5-GMP-GATE — an mpz link+RUN smoke against the staged libgmp.so via an explicit B4-loader
#     invocation (no /lib64 symlink dependency).
#
# DOCUMENTED DIVERGENCES from production packages/gmp (revisit when gcc-15.2.0-glibc seals):
#   * --disable-cxx (prod --enable-cxx): R12 only carries a MUSL-built libstdc++.a; linking it into
#     a glibc-dynamic libgmpxx.so is the R4 silent-corruption mixing hazard.  -> no libgmpxx.so /
#     gmpxx.h / gmpxx.pc, and runtime_deps drop `subsetOf gcc [libstdcpp, libgcc]`.
#   * base-leaf set trimmed to the proven B5 tool set (perl/file/bzip2/gzip are gmp-build-inert).
#
# -Wl,--build-id=none + -ffile-prefix-map + prod CFLAGS keep the artifact reproducible for the B6
# differential proof.  Pin nothing here.
